column5: went out this A.M. Launched out of Ashbridges.. gorgeous conditons except cold water.. still manged two nice kings on spoons down 50 over 195 to 210'  both of riggers... no interest in the lead core
Nice catch!!!!! and yes the water is still very cold off port darlington too.....39 degrees at 40ft  thats freezing,no bait & no kings for me today....cheers

Nice looking fish there PP. We were out this morning out of Bluffers Park and got a couple Kings around 60 down over 110. A few Rainbow as well but then everything shut right down at about 9AM. Hoping to get out again tomorrow.  Cheers
